Description: An issue was discovered in GoPro gpmf-parser before 1.2.1. There is a divide-by-zero error in GPMF_ScaledData in GPMF_parser.c.

Name: CVE-2018-18194
Description: An issue was discovered in libgig 4.1.0. There is a heap-based buffer over-read in DLS::Region::GetSample() in DLS.cpp.

Name: CVE-2018-18195
Description: An issue was discovered in libgig 4.1.0. There is an FPE (divide-by-zero error) in DLS::Sample::Sample in DLS.cpp.

Name: CVE-2018-18197

Name: CVE-2018-18198
Description: The $opener_input_field variable in addons/mediapool/pages/index.php in REDAXO 5.6.3 is not effectively filtered and is output directly to the page. The attacker can insert XSS payloads via an index.php?page=mediapool/media&opener_input_field=[XSS] request.

Description: Mediamanager in REDAXO before 5.6.4 has XSS.

IBM X-Force ID: 150096.

Name: CVE-2018-18200
Description: There is a SQL injection in Benutzerverwaltung in REDAXO before 5.6.4.

Name: CVE-2018-18201
Description: qibosoft V7.0 allows CSRF via admin/index.php?lfj=member&action=addmember to add a user account.

Name: CVE-2018-18202
Description: The QLogic 4Gb Fibre Channel 5.5.2.6.0 and 4/8Gb SAN 7.10.1.20.0 modules for IBM BladeCenter have an undocumented support account with a support password, an undocumented diags account with a diags password, and an undocumented prom account with a prom password.

Name: CVE-2018-18203
Description: A vulnerability in the update mechanism of Subaru StarLink Harman head units 2017, 2018, and 2019 may give an attacker (with physical access to the vehicle's USB ports) the ability to rewrite the firmware of the head unit. This occurs because the device accepts modified QNX6 filesystem images (as long as the attacker obtains access to certain Harman decryption/encryption code) as a consequence of a bug where unsigned images pass a validity check. An attacker could potentially install persistent malicious head unit firmware and execute arbitrary code as the root user.
